com.diffplug.common.base

Class StackDumper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.diffplug.common.base.StackDumper

  • public class StackDumper
extends Object
    Utility methods for dumping the stack - arbitrarily or at specific trigger points (such as when a certain string prints to console).

    If someone is printing "junk" to the console and you can't figure out why, try StackDumper.dumpWhenSysOutContains("junk").

      • wrapAndDumpWhenContains

        public static PrintStream wrapAndDumpWhenContains(PrintStream source,
                                                  String trigger)
        Returns a PrintStream which will redirect all of its output to the source PrintStream. If the trigger string is passed through the wrapped PrintStream, then it will dump the stack trace of the call that printed the trigger.
        Parameters:
        source - the returned PrintStream will delegate to this stream
        trigger - the string which triggers a stack dump
        Returns:
        a PrintStream with the above properties
